4	// subprocess (cwd = this task dir) bounded by `agent_preprocessing_timeout`,
5	// BEFORE any agent. It absorbs everything about the nightly refresh that is
6	// dependency-free code — so most nights are AGENTLESS and quiet, and an agent is
7	// requested only when real judgment is left (owner decision, 2026-07-23):
8	//
9	//   agent requested  ⇔  a pending AGENTIC migration note exists
10	//                    OR  the converge changed things AND check_the_world is not green.
11	//   no change, or changed-but-green with no agentic note  →  agentless night.
12	//
13	// What it does, Action-side, over the one sanctioned non-MCP surface (the Action
14	// GITHUB_TOKEN in env) and a direct PUBLIC canon fetch (owner §10: canon is
15	// public — no token, no tarball channel):
16	//   1. shallow-clone canon at its head sha (then drop .git → a rootless tree, so
17	//      apply-vendor-set skips the ancestry guards that a shallow clone can't
18	//      satisfy — it is head by construction);
19	//   2. run the CLONED canon's vendoring/apply-vendor-set.mjs to converge
20	//      .claudinite/shared/ and stamp it (compute+apply, one snapshot);
21	//   3. run the cloned converge-wiring.mjs (scheduler workflow + hashed cron,
22	//      settings hooks, retired-import removal);
23	//   4. apply the MECHANICAL migration notes (aliases/materialize/rewrite) via the
24	//      cloned migrations/apply.mjs — idempotent;
25	//   5. detect pending AGENTIC notes (registry.mjs `agenticMigrations`, gated on
26	//      the prior stamp day, same-day inclusive #330) and, if any, HOLD the stamp
27	//      at the day before the earliest one so the agent still sees the note (the
28	//      stamp/agentic coupling rule);
29	//   6. deliver the converge as ONE commit on the per-cycle maintenance branch via
30	//      NATIVE git (find the family's open PR by head-branch prefix and reuse it,
31	//      else mint a dated branch and open the PR), arming auto-merge per the
32	//      member's `maintenance.delivery`;
33	//   7. request the agent (write CLAUDINITE_REQUEST_AGENT) only when judgment is
34	//      left — the scheduler files `ready-for-agent` iff this file appears (§3,
35	//      conditional handoff). NO code→agent data channel: the file is a pure
36	//      control signal; the agent discovers its work by reading the repo (the
37	//      pushed branch, the held stamp, the pending note).
38	//
39	// Self-contained — imports only node builtins statically (the pack-independence
40	// barrier forbids reaching into the engine). The vendoring/migrations machinery
41	// is canon-internal (vendoring/ is never vendored, #385), so the worker INVOKES
42	// the freshly-fetched canon's scripts as subprocesses and DYNAMIC-imports its
43	// registry from the temp clone path — never a static import of engine code.
44	//
45	// This SUPERSEDES the per-cycle maintenance-branch naming of PR #407 (that PR
46	// reworked the OLD fleet-apply MCP path; baselining's delivery is native git
47	// Action-side and carries its own prefix/find-by-prefix here).
